---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About Us | WM Smile Generation Uganda Limited">
    <main>
        <!-- Page Header Section -->
        <section class="relative h-64 flex items-center justify-center text-center text-white">
            <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-cover bg-center" style="background-image: url('images/logo5.jpg');"></div>
            <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black opacity-60"></div>
            <div class="relative px-4">
                <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold">Our Story, Our Commitment</h1>
                <p class="text-lg mt-2">The journey behind our mission to empower Uganda's youth.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- The Founder's Story -->
        <section class="py-20 md:py-28 brownish-gradient">
            <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
                    <div class="order-2 md:order-1">
                        <img src="/images/ceo.jfif" alt="Founder Joseph Bumpenje" class="rounded-lg shadow-2xl w-full">
                    </div>
                    <div class="order-1 md:order-2 text-center md:text-left">
                        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-stone-800 mb-4">The Story of Our Founder</h2>
                        <div class="text-lg text-stone-700 space-y-4 leading-relaxed">
                            <p>
                                Bumpenje Joseph's story is one of resilience and determination, shaped by a childhood full of adversity. After his parents left him and his five siblings to fend for themselves, they found refuge under a large tree. When the tree was cut down for development, their sanctuary was lost, but a tradition was born: they began planting trees on their birthdays, a symbol of resilience and a tribute to the shelter they lost.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Driven by a passion to ensure no child would face the same challenges he did, Joseph aspired to become a teacher. He pursued a Bachelor of Science in Education from Makerere University with a clear vision: to create an environment where vulnerable children could access free education while promoting environmental conservation.
                            </p>
                             <p>
                                Today, Joseph is a professional high school mathematics teacher, a Climate Speaker, a Foster Parent, and a community leader. He brings his life experience and unwavering compassion to WM Smile Generation, especially in his work supporting refugee children, drawing from his own journey to provide them with hope and essential aid.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Vision and Mission Section -->
        <section class="py-20 md:py-28 bg-white">
            <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
                    <div class="text-center md:text-left">
                        <h3 class="text-green-800 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Our Vision</h3>
                        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-stone-800 mb-4">A Thriving Future for Every Child</h2>
                        <p class="text-lg text-stone-700 leading-relaxed">We envision a Uganda where every child and youth has the equitable opportunity to receive a quality education, is empowered to care for their wellbeing, and lives in a sustainable environment, enabling them to become leaders of a resilient and prosperous nation.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-center md:text-left">
                         <h3 class="text-green-800 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Our Mission</h3>
                        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-stone-800 mb-4">To Nurture, Educate, and Empower</h2>
                        <p class="text-lg text-stone-700 leading-relaxed">Our mission is to provide transformative educational programs, accessible resources for refugee children, and engaging nature awareness initiatives. We work hand-in-hand with communities to build supportive ecosystems where young people can discover their potential and build a brighter future for themselves and their communities.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
